sequenceDiagram
    autonumber

    participant Client as External Client
    participant Proxy as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Upstream as Upstream Application<br/>8080/TCP HTTP localhost

    rect rgb(240, 248, 255)
        Note over Client,Upstream: Flow 1: Authenticated Request Proxying
        Client->>Proxy: HTTPS/8443 Request<br/>Auth: Bearer Token / mTLS / OIDC JWT
        Note right of Proxy: Path Filter checks<br/>--allow-paths / --ignore-paths

        alt Path matches --ignore-paths
            Proxy->>Upstream: HTTP/8080 Forward (bypass auth)<br/>No encryption (localhost)
            Upstream-->>Proxy: Response
            Proxy-->>Client: HTTPS Response
        else Path requires auth
            Proxy->>K8sAPI: POST /apis/authentication.k8s.io/v1/tokenreviews<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS 1.2+
            K8sAPI-->>Proxy: TokenReview Response<br/>(authenticated: true/false, user info)

            alt Authentication failed
                Proxy-->>Client: 401 Unauthorized
            else Authentication succeeded
                Note right of Proxy: Build ResourceAttributes<br/>from Format1 or Format2 config
                Proxy->>K8sAPI: POST /apis/authorization.k8s.io/v1/subjectaccessreviews<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS 1.2+
                K8sAPI-->>Proxy: SubjectAccessReview Response<br/>(allowed: true/false)

                alt Authorization denied
                    Proxy-->>Client: 403 Forbidden
                else Authorization granted
                    Note right of Proxy: Inject headers:<br/>x-remote-user<br/>x-remote-groups<br/>x-remote-extra-*
                    Proxy->>Upstream: HTTP/8080 Forward<br/>+ auth headers<br/>No encryption (localhost)
                    Upstream-->>Proxy: Response
                    Proxy-->>Client: HTTPS Response
                end
            end
        end
    end

    rect rgb(255, 248, 240)
        Note over Client,Upstream: Flow 2: Prometheus Metrics Scraping (Hardcoded Allow)
        participant Prom as Prometheus<br/>openshift-monitoring<br/>prometheus-k8s SA

        Prom->>Proxy: GET /metrics HTTPS/8443<br/>Auth: Bearer Token (prometheus-k8s SA)<br/>TLS 1.2+
        Note right of Proxy: TokenReview authenticates SA
        Proxy->>K8sAPI: POST TokenReview<br/>HTTPS/443
        K8sAPI-->>Proxy: Authenticated:<br/>system:serviceaccount:openshift-monitoring:prometheus-k8s
        Note right of Proxy: Hardcoded Authorizer:<br/>Always ALLOW prometheus-k8s<br/>for GET /metrics<br/>(skips SAR check)
        Proxy->>Upstream: GET /metrics HTTP/8080<br/>localhost, no auth
        Upstream-->>Proxy: Metrics Response
        Proxy-->>Prom: HTTPS Metrics Response
    end

    rect rgb(240, 255, 240)
        Note over Client,Upstream: Flow 3: OIDC Authentication (Alternative)
        Client->>Proxy: HTTPS/8443 Request<br/>Auth: Bearer JWT (OIDC)
        Note right of Proxy: OIDC Authenticator:<br/>Validates JWT via issuer discovery<br/>Extracts username/groups from claims
        Proxy->>K8sAPI: POST SubjectAccessReview<br/>HTTPS/443 (user from JWT claims)
        K8sAPI-->>Proxy: Authorization Decision
        Proxy->>Upstream: HTTP/8080 Forward<br/>+ auth headers from JWT claims
        Upstream-->>Proxy: Response
        Proxy-->>Client: HTTPS Response
    end
